1.7:
The fear of the Lord
is the beginning of knowledge;
fools despise wisdom and discipline.

3.3:
Never let loyalty and faithfulness leave you.
Tie them around your neck;
write them on the tablet of your heart.

5.19:
A loving deer, a graceful doe—
let her breasts always satisfy you;
be lost in her love forever.

6.3:
Do this, then, my son, and free yourself,
for you have put yourself in your neighbor’s power:
Go, humble yourself, and plead with your neighbor.

6.22:
When you walk here and there, they will guide you;
when you lie down, they will watch over you;
when you wake up, they will talk to you.

6.29:
So it is with the one who sleeps with
another man’s wife;
no one who touches her will go unpunished.

9.7:
The one who corrects a mocker
will bring abuse on himself;
the one who rebukes the wicked will get hurt.

12.18:
There is one who speaks rashly,
like a piercing sword;
but the tongue of the wise brings healing.

20.16:
Take his garment,
for he has put up security for a stranger;
get collateral if it is for foreigners.

24.15:
Don’t set an ambush, you wicked one,
at the camp of the righteous man;
don’t destroy his dwelling.

25.13:
To those who send him, a trustworthy envoy
is like the coolness of snow on a harvest day;
he refreshes the life of his masters.

27.13:
Take his garment,
for he has put up security for a stranger;
get collateral if it is for foreigners.

30.8:
Keep falsehood and deceitful words far from me.
Give me neither poverty nor wealth;
feed me with the food I need.

30.15:
The leech has two daughters: “Give, Give!”
Three things are never satisfied;
four never say, “Enough!”:

30.16:
Sheol; a childless womb;
earth, which is never satisfied with water;
and fire, which never says, “Enough!”
